# Python ML Training Rules

## Mandatory Pipeline Sequence
`load` → `validate (Pandera)` → `features` → `split` → `cross_validate` → `evaluate` → `fairness` → `save` → `mlflow` → `quality_gates`

## Quality Gates (ALL must pass before promotion — D-12)
| Gate | Threshold |
|------|-----------|
| Primary metric | >= defined minimum (e.g., ROC-AUC >= 0.80) |
| Regression vs prod | < 5% drop |
| Fairness DIR | >= 0.80 per protected attribute |
| Leakage check | metric < 0.99 — if >= 0.99, STOP and investigate (D-06) |
| Latency P95 | <= 1.2x current production |

## Key Rules
- Feature engineering MUST be fit on train only, transform on val/test
- `~=` compatible release pinning for all ML packages (D-05)
- SHAP background data must include both classes (D-07)
- PSI drift uses quantile-based bins, not uniform (D-08)

## Required Tests
`test_no_data_leakage`, `test_shap_consistency`, `test_fairness_disparate_impact`, `test_model_meets_quality_gate`, `test_inference_latency`
